From: lalalune <shawmakesmagic@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 02:52:36 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] Q4_POLAR: vendor PolarQuant ref kernels into ggml-base +
 ggml-cpu

ref kernels (quantize_row_q4_polar_ref, dequantize_row_q4_polar,
quantize_q4_polar) live in ggml-quants.c so type_traits[] in ggml.c
can reference them without a cross-library link edge. CPU-side
quantize_row_q4_polar dispatch and the matmul kernel
ggml_vec_dot_q4_polar_q8_0 land in ggml-cpu/quants-polar.c. Shared LUT
+ Walsh-Hadamard butterfly + xorshift32 QJL sign vector live in
ggml/src/polar_centroids.h (vendored from
packages/native-plugins/polarquant-cpu/).

Type traits for GGML_TYPE_Q4_POLAR added in both ggml.c (blck=128,
type_size=82, is_quantized=true) and ggml-cpu/ggml-cpu.c
(vec_dot_type=Q8_0, nrows=1). Quantize-dispatch case + ftype mapping
(GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_Q4_POLAR=29) wired in ggml.c.

Build verified: cmake -B /tmp/build-polar -S . succeeds with no
Q4_POLAR-specific warnings.
